#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:67
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&bovo; is a Gomoku (from Japanese <foreignphrase lang=\"ja\">五目並べ</"
#| "foreignphrase>lit. \"five points\") like game for two players, where the "
#| "opponents alternate in placing their respective pictogram on the game "
#| "board. The aim of this game is to connect five of your own pieces in an "
#| "unbroken row vertically, horizontally or diagonally."
msgid ""
"&bovo; is a Gomoku (from Japanese <foreignphrase lang=\"ja\">五目並べ</"
"foreignphrase>, <quote>five points</quote>) like game for two players, where "
"the opponents alternate in placing their respective pictogram on the game "
"board. The aim of this game is to connect five of your own pieces in an "
"unbroken row vertically, horizontally or diagonally."
msgstr ""
"Gra &bovo; odpowiada grze Gomoku (z języka Japońskiego <foreignphrase lang="
"\"ja\">五目並べ</foreignphrase> dosłownie \"pięć punktów\") dla dwóch "
"graczy, gdzie przeciwnicy naprzemiennie rozmieszczają swoje symbole na "
"planszy. Celem gry jest połączenie pięciu swoich symboli w jednym rzędzie "
"poziomo, pionowo lub ukośnie."

